70.7	Sam_Peckinpah	Sam Peckinpah	David Samuel "Sam" Peckinpah (February 21, 1925 â€“ December 28, 1984) was an American film director and screenwriter who achieved prominence following the release of the Western epic The Wild Bunch (1969). He was known for the innovative and explicit depiction of action and violence, as well as his revisionist approach to the Western genre.	
